How to install

0) Before install, this package has been tested on
        Redhat 5.1/5.2/6.0/6.1  Linux
        MkLinux
        HP-UX 10.2
        HI-UX 
 
   You may need  X11R6.3/config  to run  xmkmf .

1) Do
	setenv CERN_ROOT <<cern directory>>
	setenv LCLIBROOT <<lclib directory>>
	set path=(. $JSFROOT/bin $ROOTSYS/bin $path)
	setenv IMAKEINCLUDE "-I$JSFROOT -I$LCLIBROOT"

2) According to the version number of Pythia library, 5 or 6, 
   set configure parameters in $LCLIBROOT/config/configure.in.
   Together with the version number, location of the library and
   compiler switch must be set as shown in the file, configure.in.

   Please note that lib/libLUHADR.a is not compatible with Pythia6.
   In that case, JSF version of hadronization, JSFHadronizer, must be
   used.  lib/libTAUOLA.a is not up-to-date, but it is compatible 
   with Pythia6.

2) do 
	cd $LCLIBROOT
	make all
	make install

This will create library in $LCLIBROOT/lib.
Then 

	cd $LCLIBROOT/example/genww
	
and read a file, Readme, there to run example.



